Key Match Events: The Kings used a 15-0 run at the end of the game to win 113 to 107.
De'Aaron Fox finished with 35 points and 4 assists on 13 of 16 shooting, scoring 14 points in the final period.
Malik Monk had 20 points and 6 assists, with 10 points and 8 of 8 from the free throw line in the 4th quarter.
DeMar DeRozan had two huge steals in the final eight possessions of the game.
Domantas Sabonis had 17 points, 21 rebounds, and 7 assists.
Paul George scored 30 points and 8 rebounds for the 76ers but none in the 4th quarter.
Tyrese Maxey finished with 27 points and 7 assists.
Keon Ellis hit a big three-pointer with 1:48 to go in the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Coach Doug Christie took the team to see the Beam in person to celebrate the victory.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Golden 1 Center sounded like they were watching a playoff contest in the closing minutes.
Others: Keegan Murray missed the contest due to ankle soreness.
Joel Embiid was absent from the 76ers lineup.
